<hl>
<seg id=1> Dr. Fei Xiaotong was awarded the Magsaysay Award. </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> Xinhua News agency, Manila, August 31st, by Changyi Xong- Doctor Fei Xiaotong, a famous Chinese Socialist and a Vice Minister of The National People's Congress, was awarded the 1994 Magsaysay Award for Community Leadership here. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=3> This Grand Award Ceremony was held in the Philippine Cultural Center. </seg>
<seg id=4> The Philippine President Ramos attended the ceremony and presented this years 6 recipients with their medals and award money and official certificates. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=5> As he accepting the award, Dr. Fei Xiaotong said that,  "I will not let down my friends and neighbors who gave me support and encouragement no matter how many years and months I still have to spend on my work, I will work hard every minute and do my best to do the things that will benefit the Asian people and the people in the world and also to let the knowledge be shared to the benefit and a better future for the world." </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=6> This Magsaysay Award named after the former Philippine President Ramon Magsaysay is regarded as the Asian Nobel Award. </seg>
<seg id=7> This award has a total of 5 categories that are given out annually.  The areas covered are: Government Service, Public Service, Community Leadership, News Media, Literature and Creative Arts and International peace, etc.  These are given to those organizations or individuals who have made outstanding contributions in each of these areas. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=8> Since this Award was started in 1958 there have already been 172 individuals and 14 organizations who have received this award. </seg>
</p>
